---
/**
 * ProblemSection
 *
 * Section 2: "Post-purchase is a blind spot"
 * Describes the problem with current post-purchase experience
 * Transparent background (parallax still visible)
 */

interface Props {
  className?: string
}

const { className = '' } = Astro.props
---

<section class={`py-20 sm:py-32 ${className}`}>
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title text-center mb-6 animate-on-scroll">
      Post-purchase is a blind spot.
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed text-center animate-on-scroll">
        After delivery, most brands either go quiet or send generic marketing, leaving customers on
        their own to figure out fit, care, defects, damage, and "is this normal?"
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed text-center animate-on-scroll">
        When something does go wrong, it's reactive and fragmented—customers navigate support
        queues and confusing return flows just to reach a reasonable outcome.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Optional callout box -->
    <div
      class="mt-12 p-6 bg-white/40 backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/30 rounded-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto animate-on-scroll"
    >
      <p class="text-base text-secondary italic leading-relaxed text-center">
        Vendors don't get clean, early signals. They learn too late—when returns spike, reviews
        turn negative, or support volume increases.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
